      • addUser

        public void addUser​(java.lang.String username)
        This method is called when admin wishes to add a new user. It firsts checks if the user already exists and if such a user doesn't, then it adds the new user to both the list of user_list used in the backe nd and the list of user_list in the observable list.
        Parameters:
        username - This is the new user name of the user to be added.

      • locateUser

        public int locateUser​(java.lang.String username)
        This method searches the user list for a given user name and if it is found, it returns the index of that user within the lists.
        Parameters:
        username - This is the user name of the user we wish to locate.
        Returns:
        -1 if the user is not found. If the user is found, it returns 0 or greater, indicating its index.

      • deleteUser

        public void deleteUser​(java.lang.String username)
                throws java.util.NoSuchElementException
        This method deletes a user from the back end user list as well as the observable list if the given user to delete exists.
        Parameters:
        username - This is the user name of the user to be deleted.
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if the user name cannot be located.
